Spiroctenus is a genus of African araneomorph spiders in the family Bemmeridae. It was first described by Eug√®ne Louis Simon in 1889. Originally placed with the Ctenizidae, it was transferred to the funnel-web trapdoor spiders in 1985, and to the Bemmeridae in 2020. It is a senior synonym of Bemmeris, Bessia, and Ctenonemus.

